to the editor re alessandra stanley 's coping column spare the pradas or spoil the children june 23 in view of the evident excess that certain parents provide for their children it is sad that another article in the same section reports that the annual fee for the asser levy recreation center has risen to 75 from 25 for many who use this recreation center a 50 increase is a hardship more than ever new york is a two tier city of rich and poor and i bet that those who use asser levy also attend public schools perhaps those children of privilege described in the column should do community service at asser levy with a goal of restoring the 25 annual fee maryann mckenzie park slope brooklyn

